Reference - Journal: Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A
Reference - Title: HLA class I-restricted responses to vaccinia recognize a broad array of proteins mainly involved in virulence and viral gene regulation.
Epitope - Comments: Peptide predicted to bind the HLA-A3 supertype selected by analysis of 258 predicted ORFs from Vaccinia virus WR.
Assay - Comments: This peptide is considered a binder based on its inhibition capacity (IC50500nM) of the binding of a radiolabeled standard peptide.

Reference - Title: HLA-A*0201, HLA-A*1101, and HLA-B*0702 transgenic mice recognize numerous poxvirus determinants from a wide variety of viral gene products.

Reference - Authors: Erik Depla; Annegret Van der Aa; Brian D Livingston; Claire Crimi; Koen Allosery; Veronique De Brabandere; Jonathan Krakover; Sidharta Murthy; Manley Huang; Scott Power; Lilia Bab; Carol Dahlberg; Denise McKinney; Alessandro Sette; Scott Southwood; Ramilla Philip; Mark J Newman; Lydie Meheus
Reference - Title: Rational design of a multiepitope vaccine encoding T-lymphocyte epitopes for treatment of chronic hepatitis B virus infections.
Epitope - Comments: Sequences from 20 HBV isolates, including adr, adw, ayr, and ayw serotypes, were analyzed using text string search software to identify amino acid sequences of 8 to 11 amino acids containing human class I HLA supertype motifs. Peptide sequences that were represented in at least 45% of the HBV sequences were synthesized and tested.
